==English==
===Other spellings===
*[[Gamilaraay]]
*[[Kamilaroi]]
===Etymology===
From ''[[Gamilaraay]]'', meaning ''gamil''-having, ''[[gamil]]'' being the Gamilaraay word for "no". Other dialects and languages were similarly named after their respective words for "no", e.g. the [[Wailwan]] say ''[[wayil]]''.
===Proper noun===
'''Kamilarai'''

# An [[Australian Aboriginal]] people of [[New South Wales]].
# Their language.
===Quotations===
*'''1892,''' John Fraser, ''An Australian Language''
:The Walarai dialect differs only a little from the Kamalarai proper; so also the Wailwun, spoken by the Ngaiamba blacks; for this reason, and because they have the classification of the Kamalarai, these are regarded as only subdivisions of the great Kamalarai tribe.